In order to illuminate the detailed structural features and phase components, XRD measurement was performed. Fig. 1 a displays the XRD data of Co3O4@CuO and Co3O4@CuO@GQDs. Obviously, the diffraction peaks at 19°, 31°, 36.8°, 44.8°, 55.6°, 59.3° and 65.2° can be ascribed to the (1 1 1), (2 2 0), (3 1 1), (4 0 0), (4 2 2), (5 1 1) and (4 4 0) planes of Co3O4(JCPDS No.43–1003). And the other peaks at 32.5°, 35.5°, 38.7°, 48.7° and 61.5° are corresponded to the (1 1 0), (
